---
/**
 * context-engineering 0009 · Figure 5 — M3 "where access control belongs"
 * diagram (prompt rule vs retrieval-query filter).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0009-context-caching-ordering-and-security.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes. In an .astro file the SVG is
 * plain HTML, so it renders byte-for-byte.
 *
 * The source page defined the arrowhead markers ONCE in a shared <defs> block at
 * the top of the document <body>. This figure references `arwR` and `arwG`, so
 * those two markers are inlined into its own <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 210"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Access control enforced in the retrieval query by tenant id, contrasted with the wrong approach of asking the prompt to self-restrict."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Where access control belongs</text
        >
        <!-- wrong path -->
        <rect
            x="30"
            y="36"
            width="270"
            height="150"
            rx="10"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="165" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >&#10007; In the prompt (not a boundary)</text
        >
        <rect x="50" y="68" width="230" height="30" rx="6" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="165" y="87" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110"
            >retrieve across ALL tenants</text
        >
        <line x1="165" y1="98" x2="165" y2="116" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <rect x="50" y="118" width="230" height="30" rx="6" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="165" y="137" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#111110"
            >"only answer about the user's own data"</text
        >
        <text
            x="165"
            y="170"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#9a2417">cross-tenant data already in context &rarr; leak</text
        >
        <!-- right path -->
        <rect
            x="340"
            y="36"
            width="270"
            height="150"
            rx="10"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="475" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >&#10003; In the retrieval query</text
        >
        <rect x="360" y="68" width="230" height="30" rx="6" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="475" y="87" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110"
            >filter by tenant_id + ACL at the index</text
        >
        <line x1="475" y1="98" x2="475" y2="116" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <rect x="360" y="118" width="230" height="30" rx="6" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="475" y="137" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110"
            >only the user's docs ever retrieved</text
        >
        <text
            x="475"
            y="170"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#2f5d3a">other tenants' data never reaches the model</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Pre-filter by <code>tenant_id</code> / ACL <em
            >in the retrieval query, before anything reaches the model</em
        >. A prompt instruction is a suggestion the model can ignore or be tricked past — it is not
        an access boundary.<sup><a href="#s5" id="r5b">5</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
